        "content": "<p>What's a good way to say that a type has just one element?<br>\nWe could do</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"bp\">∃!</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"n\">α</span><span class=\"o\">,</span> <span class=\"n\">True</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>but is there a more direct way, something like this?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code> <span class=\"n\">isSingletonType</span> <span class=\"n\">α</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
